@{
    ViewBag.Title = "Home Page";
}
@section featured {
    <section class="featured">
        <div class="content-wrapper">
            <hgroup class="title">
                <h1>@ViewBag.Title.</h1>
                <h2>@ViewBag.Message</h2>
            </hgroup>
            <p>
                This Web application is a template used to experiment with technology stack and good practices.
                This should only contain a minimum of data and can have multiple pages for each of the technology/practices being used.
            </p>
        </div>
    </section>
}
<h3>List of experiments:</h3>
<ol class="round">
    <li class="one">
        <h5>MVC Stack</h5>
        Using a full stack which includes Entity Framework - Repository Pattern - Structure Map - Service Layer - MVC 4.<br />
        This @Html.ActionLink("page", "Index", "Publication") contains a list of Publications and some simple binding examples.<br />
        VS2012 Automatically includes css and js optimization using <a href="http://codebetter.com/howarddierking/2012/06/04/web-optimization-in-visual-studio-2012-rc/">Web Grease</a>.</br>
        Seems to automatically include <a href="http://modernizr.com/">modernizr</a> which may not be required for all projects. It is used to test html5 browser compatibility.<br />
        Also seems to contain <a href="http://knockoutjs.com/">knockout</a> an open source java library used to separate data from UI and implement the <a href="http://addyosmani.com/blog/understanding-mvvm-a-guide-for-javascript-developers/">MVVM pattern</a>.<br />
        Publication edit code contains client side validation using jquery validate as well as server side validation through the model attributes.<br />
    </li>

    <li class="two">
        <h5>Bootstrap</h5>
        Bootstrap is to be used as the front-end framework so jquery-ui files were removed from the default Microsoft MVC4 template.<br />
        More to come...
    </li>

    <li class="three">
        <h5>OAuth</h5>
        To be Implemented...
    </li>
</ol>
